<DocsPage
  title="MCP Sidecar"
  section="Architecture"
  description="Model Context Protocol server for in-editor insights."
>
  <p>
    The Primer MCP sidecar is a Model Context Protocol server that gives Claude Code direct
    access to your team's usage data during conversations — no context switching required.
  </p>

  <h2>Available Tools</h2>

  <p>The sidecar exposes 5 tools to Claude:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>sync</code></td>
        <td>Upload any local sessions that haven't been synced yet. Useful after offline work.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>my_stats</code></td>
        <td>Personal usage analytics: session counts, token usage, tools used, and outcomes.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>team_overview</code></td>
        <td>Team-level analytics: aggregate usage, costs, and outcome distribution.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>friction_report</code></td>
        <td>Friction points your team encounters most frequently, with type and count.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>recommendations</code></td>
        <td>Actionable recommendations based on usage patterns and friction analysis.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Installation</h2>

  <p>Add the sidecar to <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>:</p>

  <pre><code>&#123;
  "mcpServers": &#123;
    "primer": &#123;
      "command": "python",
      "args": ["-m", "primer.mcp.server"],
      "env": &#123;
        "PRIMER_SERVER_URL": "http://localhost:8000",
        "PRIMER_API_KEY": "primer_...",
        "PRIMER_ADMIN_API_KEY": "your-admin-key"
      &#125;
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <p>
    After saving, restart Claude Code. The Primer tools will appear in Claude's tool list.
  </p>

  <h2>Authentication</h2>

  <p>The sidecar uses two keys depending on the tool:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong><code>PRIMER_API_KEY</code></strong> — Your engineer API key. Used by <code>sync</code>
      and <code>my_stats</code> to authenticate as you.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong><code>PRIMER_ADMIN_API_KEY</code></strong> — Admin key. Used by <code>team_overview</code>,
      <code>friction_report</code>, and <code>recommendations</code> to access team-wide data.
      Falls back to <code>PRIMER_API_KEY</code> if not set.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Example Usage</h2>

  <p>Once registered, you can ask Claude questions like:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>"What are my top friction points this week?"</li>
    <li>"How does our team's token usage compare to last month?"</li>
    <li>"What recommendations do you have for improving our AI workflow?"</li>
    <li>"Sync my recent sessions and show me my stats."</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Claude will call the appropriate Primer tools and return insights inline.</p>

  <h2>Running Manually</h2>

  <p>You can run the MCP server directly to test it:</p>

  <pre><code>PRIMER_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8000 \
PRIMER_API_KEY=primer_... \
PRIMER_ADMIN_API_KEY=primer-admin-dev-key \
python -m primer.mcp.server</code></pre>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>

  <p>
    The sidecar is built with <code>FastMCP</code> and makes HTTP calls to the Primer REST API
    using <code>httpx</code>. It has no persistent state — all data lives in the API server.
  </p>

  <pre><code>Claude Code
  └── MCP tool call (e.g., team_overview)
        └── primer.mcp.tools.primer_team_overview()
              └── httpx GET /api/v1/analytics/overview
                    └── Returns JSON string to Claude</code></pre>

  <p>
    The sidecar is lightweight and runs locally alongside Claude Code, one instance per
    developer machine.
  </p>

  <h2>Source</h2>

  <p>
    The MCP implementation lives in <code>src/primer/mcp/</code>:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><code>server.py</code> — FastMCP app, tool registration</li>
    <li><code>tools.py</code> — Tool implementations with httpx calls</li>
  </ul>
</DocsPage>
